            "body": "German etiquette psychology is based on the concept of 'Sachlichkeit,' meaning practicality and objectivity. What matters most is keeping professional and private spheres separate, along with a deep respect for order (Ordnung). Social relationships are built on trust that comes from competence and predictability, not just surface-level politeness. Understanding these mechanisms makes it possible to function effectively in Germany’s social and business structures while minimizing the risk of misunderstandings caused by cultural differences in perceptions of time and direct communication.",
