          "culturalNote": {
            "body": "American etiquette is deeply rooted in the Puritan work ethic and Enlightenment ideals of individual freedom. Unlike hierarchical systems, the psychology of behavior in the USA is based on the concept of the 'self-made man' and an apparent informality intended to reduce power distance. Understanding that politeness here serves efficiency and optimism is key to navigating interpersonal and professional relationships effectively on this continent.",
            "title": "Cultural Note"
          },
