          "culturalContext": "Brazil",
          "culturalNote": {
            "body": "In Brazil, personal hygiene is treated with almost religious zeal and forms the foundation of social acceptance. Due to the tropical climate and cultural heritage, standards of cleanliness are much higher here than in many countries in Europe or North America. Brushing your teeth in public places after a meal or bathing several times a day is not a luxury, but a social obligation. Neglecting these aspects is interpreted as a lack of respect for others and may result in immediate exclusion from social and professional circles.",
            "title": "Cultural Note"
          },
